text: Sturt Parish Pool County (NSW)Sturt Parish is a remote civil parish of Poole County in far North West New South Wales,/ Map of the County of Poole : Western Division, , located at . ==Geography== The Geography, of Sturt is mostly the flat, arid landscape of the Channel Country. The nearest town is Tibooburra to the east, which is on the Silver City Highway and lies south of the Sturt National Park.Olive Downs campground. ==History== The Parish is on the traditional lands of the WadigaliAboriginal Heritage , Corner Country History & Heritage. and to a lesser extent Karenggapa,Tindale, Norman Barnett (1974).
